Russia , U.S. Sign Accord on Aid Package
MOSCOW , December 23 ( Xinhua ) -- Russia and the United States on Wednesday signed a package of documents on U.S. humanitarian assistance to Russia , the Itar-Tass news agency reported .
The documents signed here by Russian Deputy Prime Minister Gennady Kulik and U.S. Charge d ' Affaires John Teft .
Under the accords , the United States will provide 600 million dollars worth of food , including 500,000 tons of maize , 500,000 tons of soybeans and soya meal , 200,000 tons of wheat and 120,000 tons of meat .
According to the Russian Statistics Committee , agricultural production in the first 11 months of the year dropped by 9 percent and the country registered the worst harvest in more than four decades .
Russia 's gross grain harvest in 1998 was 48.5 billion tons under preliminary reports , 45.3 percent down from the previous year 's figure of 88.6 million tons .
